                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/691.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister for Foreign Affairs of the
                            Revolutionary Government</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName> (<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1911-12-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1911-12-12T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>; received <hi
                            rend="italic">December 13, 1911</hi>).</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your assistance is urgently requested to prevent misunderstanding arising in
                    America and China by restraining financiers loaning funds to Manchus, which
                    independent Provinces must regard as directed against them in their fight for
                    liberty. The Manchu contention that the money is needed to maintain order in
                    Peking is a ruse. Foreigners can increase legation guards or remove temporarily
                    to Tientsin. The revolutionaries are giving the fullest protection to
                    foreigners.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wu Ting Fang</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
